# Lookml To Sigma

This repository converts LookML explores and views into Sigma Data Model JSON. It runs locally: no dbt-converter dependency. You get API-ready JSON under `sigma_model/` and can optionally push models to Sigma with `create_model.py`.

> Generated by `make_readme.sh` on 2026-03-13 05:59:09 UTC.

## What this repo does

At a high level:

1. Store or generate LookML under `looker_files/<project_name>/` (sample: `create_lookml.sh` creates `looker_files/plugs/`; or add your own folder; or import a zip via `import_lookml.sh`).
2. Run `setup.sh` to install dependencies and convert each LookML project under `looker_files/` to Sigma JSON via `tools/build_sigma_explore_json.py` (uses `lkml` and `pyyaml` only).
3. Outputs go to `sigma_model/<project_name>/*.json` (one JSON per LookML model file).
4. Optionally run `create_model.py` to create data models in Sigma from those JSON files. Push to GitHub is optional and prompted at the end of setup.

